{
  "stem": "10572.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I told my father [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] that I had affidavits, or the promise for affidavits, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] my father told me that this was too serious a thing to joke about.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because he didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- we drove-- drove home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the next day, I-- I went to our rabbi, who was a relatively new rabbi, young-- young rabbi, was a good friend of mine, Josef Schwartz, who later on ended up to be a rabbi in Benton Harbor, Michigan after going to Manila and being a prisoner of the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And asked him to write a letter to Mrs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Hamilton as a reference, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because my father was skeptic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Told me, sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Said, she's coming back home to America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she will tell her husband what she has done here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and he will say to her, are you completely meshuggah?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bring four people over here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You are responsible for them?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I sat down, and I wrote a letter thanking her and-- and sending her a book about my-- about Hildesheim, which was magnificent.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was one of the most beautiful cities.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she knew it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so now I waited and waited.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the 23rd of August, 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the 23rd of September happened and nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't hear.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father, knowing [LAUGHS] the ways of the world, said, you know, forget about the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] There was an old saying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] [NON-ENGLISH] is when you have second thoughts about something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And said, she went back and-- so on the 6th of October, I got the letter-- the letter.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a long, long, letter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you will find the letter in my story that I wrote in memory of Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hamilton.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
